SIMPLE: puppet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puppet
<hw>Pup"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>popet</ets>,
OF. <ets>poupette</ets>; akin to F. <ets>poup⟦eacute⟧e</ets> a doll,
probably from L. <ets>puppa</ets>, <ets>pupa</ets>, a girl, doll,
puppet. Cf. <er>Poupeton</er>, <er>Pupa</er>, <er>Pupil</er>,
<er>Puppy</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also <asp>poppet</asp>.]</altsp>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A small image in the human form; a doll.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1164 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A similar figure moved by the hand or by a wire in a
mock drama; a marionette; a wooden actor in a play.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At the pipes of some carved organ move,⟦br⟧
The gilded <qex>puppets</qex> dance.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One controlled in his action by the will of another;
a tool; -- so used in contempt.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>The upright support for the
bearing of the spindle in a lathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Puppet master</b></col>. <cd>Same as
<er>Puppetman</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Puppet play</b></col>, <cd>a puppet
show.</cd> -- <col><b>Puppet player</b></col>, <cd>one who manages the
motions of puppets.</cd> -- <col><b>Puppet show</b></col>, <cd>a mock
drama performed by puppets moved by wires.</cd> -- <col><b>Puppet
valve</b></col>, <cd>a valve in the form of a circular disk, which
covers a hole in its seat, and opens by moving bodily away from the seat
while remaining parallel with it, -- used in steam engines, pumps,
safety valves, etc. Its edge is often beveled, and fits in a conical
recess in the seat when the valve is closed. See the valves shown in
<xex>Illusts.</xex> of <cref>Plunger pump</cref>, and <cref>Safety
valve</cref>, under <er>Plunger</er>, and <er>Safety</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puppetish</ent>⟦br⟧
